════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 6 — RULES — DO NOT VIOLATE ANY OF THESE
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. app-background renders ONCE in app.component — never 
   inside individual page components. Adding it inside 
   landing, persona, or ecosystem will create duplicate 
   canvases and kill performance.

2. All page components have background: transparent — 
   the global canvas shows through everything.

3. Three.js canvas z-index: 1 — always below page content 
   which is z-index: 10+. If content disappears, check 
   z-index stacking.

4. The loaderComplete event is the ONLY trigger for the 
   hero reveal. Never use ngOnInit or a hardcoded timeout 
   as the trigger.

5. hero-section starts with visibility: hidden — not 
   opacity: 0. Opacity 0 still takes up space and can 
   interfere with the loader. Visibility hidden removes 
   it from paint entirely.

6. #00C896 is the ONLY accent color used anywhere across 
   all three pages. No orange, no purple, no multi-color 
   stats. One color, everywhere.

7. CST badge green (#00873C) appears ONLY on the badge 
   square. It is NOT used as text color, CTA color, 
   or accent anywhere.

8. "A lot / quietly / happened." must be on THREE separate 
   lines using flex-direction: column on .hero-heading. 
   Do not let the browser collapse them onto one line.

9. font-family 'Syne' for all headings, 'Inter' for all 
   body text. If these fonts are not already imported, 
   add to index.html:
   <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
   <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?
     family=Syne:wght@700;800&
     family=Inter:wght@300;400;500&
     display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

10. ngOnDestroy in BackgroundComponent must cancel the 
    animation frame and dispose all Three.js objects. 
    Missing this will cause memory leaks on route changes.

